Subject: [PATCH] feat(sign): cortex sync callback + cortex_proposal_id in
 Stripe reference
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

When this folder was generated by Cortex (source.cortexProposalId stamped in
client.json), we now:

- Pass the Cortex proposal id as Stripe's `client_reference_id` on the
  checkout redirect. Cortex's Stripe webhook matches on this so paid events
  automatically link back to the proposal record.
- Fire a fire-and-forget `POST` to Cortex `/api/webhooks/docs/signed` right
  after the KV write, so /admin/proposals/[slug] flips to "Signed" without
  waiting for manual reconciliation.

Also: _headers now sets `Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors …cortex.*`
and drops X-Frame-Options: DENY so Cortex's admin preview iframe works.

New CF env vars (set in Pages project → Settings → Environment variables):
  CORTEX_WEBHOOK_URL   e.g. https://cortex.nativz.io
  DOCS_WEBHOOK_SECRET  same value as Cortex's Vercel env

Branch cortex-sync; do not merge until Cortex's DOCS_WEBHOOK_SECRET is set.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
